<br>
If the technology exists to get music online, they why doesn't the recording industry offer that to consumers? I would be willing to pay a monthly fee to be able to pick and choose songs to download and burn. I might even be persuaded to pay a per-song fee if I'm allowed to burn them and play them in my cd players, but don't force me to buy an entire cd of crap for one good song. <br>
<br>
I'm really hoping the new Napster can make this happen. <br>
<br>
/crosses fingers<br>
