Hurm.  I don't see the double standard.  Both sides are being required to follow copyright laws whereby the owner of the intellectual property gets reimbursement through whatever means are appropriate, be it movie tickets, CD sales, purchased downloads, what have you.  You can argue until you are blue in the face that the recording industry charges too much for their goods.  And you may very well be right.  But...so what?  They *own* the copyright; it is theirs to do that with.  And if the price is unreasonable, you have the right to not purchase it.  What you don't get the right to do, just because the cost of a luxury item is too high, is steal it and claim the moral high ground.<br>
