<br>
In a system where you have only one source to experience new music (the radio) this isn't a problem.  The station will play the same 40 songs over and over and eventually you will start to like a few and go out and purchase a CD.  This is great for the record companies becuase it alows them to maximize profits, while simultaneously reducing cost.  If they only have to pay to promote one new face or one new song with the certain expectaion that eager teens everywhere will turn out in droves to throw money at them, then that's what they will do.<br>
